This species is known from most of southern Europe, Maghreb, Turkey , Syria , and Jordan ( cf .
Nardi 2004 c
;
Uhmann et al . 2005
). In the global distribution of this species,
Bucciarelli ( 1961 : 125 )
listed also the Caucasus (without further detail), but later he (
Bucciarelli 1980
) and all other authors did not include this region. The above listed old specimens suggest a possible occurrence of this species in the Caucasian countries.
